trend_summary: Small-scale infill and commercial expansions occurred while the road grid stayed constant. Tree canopy slightly increased, especially around stream corridors. Industrial blocks in the south-central zone were reconfigured, and parking areas enlarged. The riverside reservoir showed fluctuating water extent and color, hinting at drawdowns or sediment pulses. Overall land-use remains predominantly low-rise residential.
notable_changes: South-central industrial campus enlarged and re-laid out, replacing older warehouses.
New parking lots and roof retrofits around the northern stadium/arena complex.
Reservoir on the west bank alternates between full, drawdown and turbid conditions.
Cleared patches along creek edges later revegetated, boosting riparian green space.
Scattered residential lots added within existing street network, modestly raising housing count.
